<p><b>Allen Carr</b> (2 September 1934 – 29 November 2006) was most notable as the <a href="/wiki/Author" title="Author">author</a> of books on how to stop <a href="/wiki/Tobacco_smoking" title="Tobacco smoking">smoking</a> (having stopped smoking after 31 years as a five-pack-per-day <a href="/wiki/Chain_smoking" title="Chain smoking">chain smoker</a>) and, as he stressed, escape <a href="/wiki/Nicotine" title="Nicotine">nicotine</a> <a href="/wiki/Addiction" title="Addiction">addiction</a>.</p>
